spLocks noGrp="1"/></p:cNvSpPr><p:nvPr><p:ph type="body" idx="1"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="962592" y="2247900"/><a:ext cx="15953807" cy="7879080"/></a:xfrm></p:spPr><p:txBody><a:bodyPr/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="4400" b="1" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:schemeClr val="tx1"/></a:solidFill><a:highlight><a:srgbClr val="00FFFF"/></a:highlight><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:rPr><a:t>Empathize Phase</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="4400" dirty="0"><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:rPr><a:t>From the user study, we understood that unemployment is not only caused by lack of jobs, but mainly due to lack of awareness, proper guidance, and access to relevant skill development opportunities.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="4400" dirty="0"><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:rPr><a:t>Many youth feel confused about career direction, unaware of in-demand skills, and unable to navigate existing job platforms effectively. Language barriers and limited digital exposure further increase this gap.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="4400" dirty="0"><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:rPr><a:t>This insight highlighted the need for a personalized, accessible, and intelligent system that guides youth step-by-step from skill identification to employment</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:endParaRPr lang="en-IN" sz="2800" dirty="0"><a:latin typeface="+mn-lt"/></a:endParaRPr></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree><p:extLst><p:ext uri="{BB962C8B-B14F-4D97-AF65-F5344CB8AC3E}"><p14:creationId xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main" val="1028198211"/></p:ext></p:extLst></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>